---
import Layout from '../components/Layout.astro';
import Navigation from '../components/Navigation';
import Footer from '../components/Footer';
import '../styles/globals.css';
import { FiWind, FiShield, FiDollarSign, FiAward, FiUsers, FiTrendingUp } from 'react-icons/fi';
---

<Layout
  title="About Mentis Aura - Philosophy Without Compromise"
  description="The breeze of mind. Independent philosophical publishing without algorithms, committees, or compromise."
>
  <Navigation client:load />

  <main class="min-h-screen">
    <!-- Hero Section -->
    <section class="bg-gradient-to-br from-slate-800 to-slate-900 text-white py-24 px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 relative overflow-hidden">
      <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-5">
        <div class="absolute inset-0" style="background-image: radial-gradient(circle, white 1px, transparent 1px); background-size: 30px 30px;"></div>
      </div>
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center relative z-10">
        <div class="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-20 h-20 bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-400 to-blue-600 rounded-2xl mb-8 shadow-xl">
          <FiWind className="w-10 h-10 text-white" />
        </div>
        <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-6xl font-bold mb-6 font-playfair">About Mentis Aura</h1>
        <p class="text-2xl md:text-3xl text-slate-200 font-playfair italic">The Breeze of Mind</p>
        <div class="mt-8 flex items-center justify-center gap-8 text-sm text-slate-300">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
            <div class="w-2 h-2 bg-blue-400 rounded-full"></div>
            <span>Philosophy Without Compromise</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
            <div class="w-2 h-2 bg-blue-400 rounded-full"></div>
            <span>Direct-to-Reader</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Main Content -->
    <section class="py-16 px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 bg-white">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-gray-700 space-y-8">
          <div>
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6 font-playfair">Mentis Aura. The Breeze of Mind.</h2>
            <p>
              Like wind carrying seeds across distances, ideas move most freely when unobstructed. Not forced through algorithms. Not filtered by committees seeking consensus. Not shaped to maximize engagement.
            </p>
            <p>
              A breeze moves naturally, touching what it touches, leaving other things undisturbed. Some feel it immediately. Others notice only when leaves rustle. Some turn toward it. Others turn away.
            </p>
            <p>
              This is how philosophy should travelâ€”from thinker to reader, directly, naturally, without intermediaries dictating its path or softening its edge.
            </p>
            <p class="font-semibold text-gray-900 text-xl">
              We are the breeze. The work is what it carries.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="border-t border-gray-200 pt-8">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6 font-playfair">Why Direct-to-Reader?</h2>
            <p>
              Traditional publishing requires compromise. Committees determine what's "marketable." Algorithms decide what readers see. The loudest voices drown out challenging thought.
            </p>
            <p>
              When philosophical work must prove its commercial viability before publication, entire categories of inquiry disappear. Controversial perspectives get softened. Difficult ideas get simplified. Challenging readers becomes risky.
            </p>
            <p class="font-semibold">
              Philosophy requires infrastructure equal to its ambition.
            </p>
            <p>
              We built that infrastructure. Print-on-demand eliminates warehouse costs demanding bestseller velocity. Direct sales remove platform algorithms deciding who sees philosophical work. No editorial committees softening edges to broaden appeal.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="border-t border-gray-200 pt-8">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-8 font-playfair text-center">What We Offer Readers</h2>
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
              <div class="group bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-50 to-blue-100 p-8 rounded-2xl border-2 border-blue-200 hover:shadow-xl transition-all duration-300 hover:-translate-y-1">
                <div class="flex items-center justify-center w-14 h-14 bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-500 to-blue-600 rounded-xl mb-4 shadow-lg">
                  <FiShield className="w-7 h-7 text-white" />
                </div>
                <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3 text-xl">No Compromise on Content</h3>
                <p class="mb-0 text-gray-700">
                  Books published as written. No editorial intervention to make ideas more palatable. No committee decisions about what's "too controversial."
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="group bg-gradient-to-br from-green-50 to-green-100 p-8 rounded-2xl border-2 border-green-200 hover:shadow-xl transition-all duration-300 hover:-translate-y-1">
                <div class="flex items-center justify-center w-14 h-14 bg-gradient-to-br from-green-500 to-green-600 rounded-xl mb-4 shadow-lg">
                  <FiDollarSign className="w-7 h-7 text-white" />
                </div>
                <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3 text-xl">Fair Pricing</h3>
                <p class="mb-0 text-gray-700">
                  No retail markup. No middlemen taking cuts. You pay for production, shipping, and the work itself. Nothing more.
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="group bg-gradient-to-br from-purple-50 to-purple-100 p-8 rounded-2xl border-2 border-purple-200 hover:shadow-xl transition-all duration-300 hover:-translate-y-1">
                <div class="flex items-center justify-center w-14 h-14 bg-gradient-to-br from-purple-500 to-purple-600 rounded-xl mb-4 shadow-lg">
                  <FiAward className="w-7 h-7 text-white" />
                </div>
                <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3 text-xl">Quality Production</h3>
                <p class="mb-0 text-gray-700">
                  Each book printed fresh when ordered. Premium materials. Professional binding. Books meant to last, not disposable products.
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="group bg-gradient-to-br from-orange-50 to-orange-100 p-8 rounded-2xl border-2 border-orange-200 hover:shadow-xl transition-all duration-300 hover:-translate-y-1">
                <div class="flex items-center justify-center w-14 h-14 bg-gradient-to-br from-orange-500 to-orange-600 rounded-xl mb-4 shadow-lg">
                  <FiUsers className="w-7 h-7 text-white" />
                </div>
                <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3 text-xl">Direct Support for Philosophy</h3>
                <p class="mb-0 text-gray-700">
                  Your purchase directly funds philosophical work. No corporate shareholders. No conglomerate profits. Just ideas and the infrastructure supporting them.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="border-t border-gray-200 pt-8">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6 font-playfair">No Committees, No Algorithms</h2>
            <p>
              You won't find our books trending on social media. Algorithms don't promote challenging philosophy. Committees don't greenlight controversial inquiry. The marketplace doesn't reward difficulty.
            </p>
            <p>
              We're fine with that.
            </p>
            <p>
              This work reaches those who seek it. Readers tired of philosophy that tip-toes around uncomfortable truths. People valuing substance over sensation. Those willing to engage seriously with ideas they may ultimately reject.
            </p>
            <p class="font-semibold">
              Small audience, serious engagement. Better than large audience, shallow consumption.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="border-t border-gray-200 pt-8">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6 font-playfair">Building for Decades, Not Quarters</h2>
            <p>
              Traditional publishers think in quarters. We think in decades.
            </p>
            <p>
              A catalog of serious philosophical work takes time to build. Each book requires years of thought, not months of production. Readers discover difficult philosophy slowly, through word-of-mouth and serious engagement, not viral marketing.
            </p>
            <p>
              We're patient. Philosophy has always moved at its own pace.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="border-t border-gray-200 pt-8">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6 font-playfair">What We're Not</h2>
            <p>
              <strong>We're not self-help.</strong> If you seek transformation, comfort, or easy answers, look elsewhere.
            </p>
            <p>
              <strong>We're not academic press.</strong> No peer review. No institutional gatekeeping. Just ideas standing on their own merit.
            </p>
            <p>
              <strong>We're not building community.</strong> No social media presence. No follower counts. No personality cult around authors. The work speaks or it doesn't.
            </p>
            <p>
              <strong>We're not marketers.</strong> We describe what we publish honestly. If you disagree with the philosophy, that's fine. Better you know before purchasing than feel misled after.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="border-t border-gray-200 pt-8 bg-slate-50 -mx-8 px-8 py-8 rounded-lg">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6 font-playfair">The Work We Publish</h2>
            <p>
              Currently: <em>The Contradicted Existence</em> by Nassim El Hassouni. Twenty-four philosophical essays examining selfishness, consciousness, free will, death, love, and the fundamental contradictions of human existence.
            </p>
            <p>
              Future: Additional philosophical works as they're ready. One to two titles annually. No rush. No compromise.
            </p>
            <p class="mb-0">
              Each work must meet one standard: Does it examine existence honestly, without softening difficult truths for commercial appeal?
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- CTA -->
        <div class="mt-16 bg-gradient-to-br from-slate-800 to-slate-900 rounded-3xl p-12 text-center shadow-2xl">
          <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4 font-playfair">Explore Our Work</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-300 text-lg mb-8 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
            Ready to engage with philosophy without compromise? Start with our first publication.
          </p>
          <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
            <a
              href="/book"
              class="group inline-flex items-center justify-center bg-blue-600 text-white px-8 py-4 rounded-xl hover:bg-blue-700 transition-all font-semibold text-lg shadow-xl hover:shadow-2xl hover:scale-105"
            >
              View The Contradicted Existence
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 ml-2 group-hover:translate-x-1 transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 7l5 5m0 0l-5 5m5-5H6"></path>
              </svg>
            </a>
            <a
              href="/contact"
              class="inline-block bg-white text-gray-900 px-8 py-4 rounded-xl hover:bg-gray-100 transition-all font-semibold text-lg shadow-lg"
            >
              Contact Us
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Philosophy Statement -->
    <section class="py-16 px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 bg-gradient-to-br from-slate-800 to-slate-900 text-white">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">
        <p class="text-2xl font-playfair italic mb-4">
          "In shadows, thought moves freely."
        </p>
        <p class="text-slate-300">
          Where thought moves freely. Philosophy without compromise.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <Footer client:load />
</Layout>
